						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Maduraikoṇḍa Parakēśarivarman, Parānthakā I, Year 32 = 939 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Built in at the bottom. Gift of land by a lady Kaṇḍi Naṅgai, a relative of certain Parakēśari Muttaraiyaṉ of Ōviyūr to the temple of Subrahmaṇyap-pḷḷaiyār, who was pleased to stand on the hill at Tiruttaṇiyal (near) Aguvūr, the eastern hamlet of Peruṅgāñji in Ōgavala-nāḍu (a district of) Melūr- kōṭṭam, which formed part of Jayaṅgoṇḍa Chōḻa-maṇḍalam. The characters of the inscription are comparatively of later period; it must be a later copy of the original.</p>						

						</summary>
